Tara Bhusan Dahal (born 18 May 1966) is a Nepali television personality, music video director and media personality based in Nepal and has been active in the Nepali television industry since 1988.

During 1988-1990 he anchored Sunday Pop, a programme of international pop music on Nepal Television (NTV), he initiated Disha Nirdesh, a political programme run on NTV anchored by Bijay Kumar, and hosted Fireside, a current affairs talk show on Kantipur Television, from 2003-2019 .

Dahal has directed  music videos for hundreds of Nepali singers, including Nima Rumba, Ramkrishna Dhakal, Rajesh Payal Rai, 1974 AD, Om Bikram Bista, Yogeswor Amatya, Nhyoo Bajracharya to name a few and the most exotic SAA KARNALI for Nepathya.
His latest show The Bravo Delta Show appears on AP1Hd television network on Wednesdays at 9pm.
